More Obituaries for Dorothea Scalise


Looking for an obituary for a different person with this name?












Dorothea Scalise


1930 - 2015
Obituary
Condolences

































 Dorothea ScaliseNov. 14, 1930 - April 27, 2015Resident of Los Altos HillsBorn in Worcester, MA to Irving McDonald and Marie (Hagerty) McDonald. Dorothea is survived by her husband of 53 years, George Scalise; children Kathy Armistead (Mike), Ted (Jeannie), Craig (Mary) and six grand children George, Katrina, Henry, JohnRegis, Mary Clare and Madeline. After a long illness, Dorothea is now reunited with her parents and five siblings, Carol, Irving, Marie, Paul and Greg.Dorothea spent much of her childhood and adolescence in a college environment, as her father was the Dean of English at Holy Cross, a Jesuit College in Worcester, MA. After graduating from Notre Dame Academy in Hingham, MA, she attended Immanuel College in Boston, MA where she doubled majored in Physics and Math. At Immanuel, Dorothea was elected student body president and was the valedictorian for her class.After graduation, she moved to Arizona to take an engineering position with Motorola. Dorothea was not only one of the first female engineers/engineering managers at Motorola, but managed a product line team where she met her future husband, George. After marrying in 1962, the couple had 3 children, moved to Geneva, Switzerland then to Los Altos Hills, California, where they have lived for 48 years.Dorothea enjoyed many activities with family and friends but her favorite pastime outside of family time was her volunteer work at Stanford hospital where she spent 15 rewarding years.
					


Published in San Jose Mercury News/San Mateo County Times on May 3, 2015


