SiBEAM Expands Executive Leadership in Engineering and Operations | Business Wire
























































SiBEAM Expands Executive Leadership in Engineering and Operations




Al Scalise and George Palmer Bring Proven Track Record of Delivering 
      High Volume Semiconductor Product Lines






May 08, 2007 09:00 AM Eastern Daylight Time



SUNNYVALE, Calif.--(BUSINESS WIRE)--SiBEAM, Inc., a leading innovator of millimeter wave (mmWave) solutions 
      and developer of high-speed wireless communications platforms, 
      today announced the appointment of two seasoned leaders to its executive 
      team.
    


      Al Scalise recently joined SiBEAM as Vice President of Systems and 
      Software Engineering with over 22 years of experience 
      in IC design, system and software development and product management. In 
      his role, Scalise will focus on developing the systems and software to 
      bring SiBEAM’s wireless solutions to customer 
      applications. As one of the inventors of HDMI, Scalise brings in 
      experience from Silicon Image where he was Director of the Design 
      Engineering team developing HDMI devices for consumer electronics 
      products. Scalise’s prior experience and 
      accomplishments include his role as Principal Engineer architecting and 
      designing digital video processing ASICs for DVDO. He also spent ten 
      years at Apple Computer as a Lead Design Engineer where he was nominated 
      for the prestigious CEO Technical Award for research and development in 
      recognition of his groundbreaking work on the Power Macintosh. He has 
      authored nine U.S. patents and has a B.S. in Electrical and Electronic 
      Engineering from the California State Polytechnic University Pomona.
    

      SiBEAM also added George Palmer to its executive leadership team as Vice 
      President of Operations. As Vice President of Operations, Palmer will be 
      responsible for manufacturing, product engineering, test engineering, 
      quality management, packaging, facilities and IT. He brings over 30 
      years of semiconductor operations, development and product management 
      experience. Most recently, Palmer worked as Vice President of Operations 
      at PortalPlayer, Inc., which was recently acquired by NVIDIA and is 
      notable for providing music player chip controllers for Apple’s 
      iPod products. He has held various leadership positions including Vice 
      President of Operations and Manufacturing at wireless company Bermai, 
      Inc., and earlier at Quantum3D, Inc., as VP of Operations and Product 
      Management. Before working with startup companies, Mr. Palmer worked at 
      National Semiconductor and Fairchild Semiconductor for 23 years managing 
      operations, development and marketing for high volume product lines 
      including PC Products, Ethernet Systems, Digital Video and 
      Microprocessors. Mr. Palmer received his degree in electrical 
      engineering and computer science from the University of California, 
      Berkeley.
    

“As SiBEAM prepares to go to market, the 
      addition of Al Scalise and George Palmer rounds out our executive team. 
      I anticipate both will make significant and immediate contributions to 
      the company,” said John LeMoncheck, SiBEAM 
      President and CEO. “Al Scalise’s 
      experience will help provide our customers with the most innovative 
      semiconductor systems solutions to revolutionize high-speed wireless 
      data transmission. George Palmer brings a distinguished background in 
      semiconductor operations and development with an unsurpassed track 
      record of proven ability to significantly ramp volume production. Both 
      executives will be critical in accelerating SiBEAM’s 
      growth and expansion into existing and emerging markets.”


About SiBEAM, Inc.
    

      Founded in 2004, SiBEAM is a fabless semiconductor company developing 
      intelligent millimeter wave technologies and leveraging the latest 
      manufacturing methods to meet the demand for high-bandwidth services. 
      SiBEAM is the first to build 60 GHz chipsets using CMOS technology. 
      SiBEAM is a founding member of the WirelessHD™ 
      special interest group and intends to support delivery of the first 
      wireless high definition digital interface for A/V networks, the first 
      of many applications for SiBEAM's innovative technology. For more 
      information please visit: www.sibeam.com.
    


Contacts

      SiBEAM, Inc.Lianne Caetano, 408-245-3120 ext. 132lcaetano@sibeam.comorStearns 
      Johnson CommunicationsPamela Njissang, 415-397-7600pnjissang@stearnsjohnson.com


















Contacts

      SiBEAM, Inc.Lianne Caetano, 408-245-3120 ext. 132lcaetano@sibeam.comorStearns 
      Johnson CommunicationsPamela Njissang, 415-397-7600pnjissang@stearnsjohnson.com







 
 

 






